description:
Using HotDoc, you can book and manage your appointments with health professionals anywhere, at any time: 
• Instantly book online with your GP, dentist, psychologist, dietitian and more 
• Access On Demand Care via Quick Consults and Telehealth
• See the availability of doctors - pick a date and time that best works for you 
• Save your care team in one place to easily book future appointments 

Stay on top of your schedule:
• View and receive reminders of your upcoming appointments
• See your place in the queue once you arrive at the clinic or practice
• Conveniently reschedule your appointment if plans change
• Receive email notifications confirming your appointment

Be in control of your and your family's health and wellbeing:
• Book a range of appointments such as dental check ups, skin checks, vaccinations and more
• Search and filter healthcare providers based on your needs such as by gender, opening hours, and bulk billing practices
• Book appointments for children and family members

About HotDoc

HotDoc is Australia’s leading Patient Engagement Platform, trusted by over 18,000 healthcare professionals and 6 million Australians to book and manage their health appointments.

We value patients privacy and the security of patient data. We never on-sell any data and only share patient information directly with your selected clinic.

Our core belief is that the best patient outcomes are achieved by maintaining the continuity of care with your trusted health practitioner.

my health is a secure and convenient way to view key health information that you, your healthcare providers or representatives have uploaded to My Health Record, it also gives you access to electronic prescriptions and has great features like find and book a health service. It’s fast, easy, and secure - and you can access and share it all from the palm of your hand. my health app is an initiative of the Australian Government.

To start using my health, you’ll need:
1.	a myGov account linked to My Health Record
2.	to have accessed your My Health Record at least once through a web browser

For help to do this, please follow all 3 steps to set up your record online - https://www.digitalhealth.gov.au/help/set-up

my health provides easy access to key health information, including:
•	electronic prescriptions and Active Script List
•	Emergency contact details
•	medicine information history
•	pathology results, including COVID-19 test results
•	proof of vaccination history and upcoming immunisations
•	allergy and reactions information
•	hospital discharge summaries
•	advance care planning documents
•	find a health service
•	link to healthdirect Australia’s symptom checker and medicines information and book a health service (where available).

Future updates
More features will be added to the app over time. Help us understand how to improve it by giving us a rating and leaving a review within App Stores. Additionally, please feel free to give us feedback by email to help@digitalhealth.gov.au

Chemist Warehouse App features:

- Prescriptions: View your dispensed medication, add electronic scripts, active script list and photo scripts to your medications list. Simply select your medicines and add it to Cart, you can request that your prescription be dispensed ahead of time, so that it can be ready for you when you arrive at the store.

- The Chemist Warehouse App doesn't require you to activate at any local Chemist Warehouse store. If you want to use full features, you will have to register at the store and an activation code will be sent directly to your phone so that you can get started immediately.

- Carer Mode on the Chemist Warehouse App which allows multiple dependants to be handled by one carer allowing the app to be a family app for managing medications.

- Refill Notifications: Notifications are sent directly to your phone to remind you when you require your prescription refilled. Reminders are also sent to remind you to see your doctor when your prescription runs out. Never run out of your medicines again!

- Dose Reminders: Notifications will remind you to take your medications at the right time, on time, every time. By recording your dosing via the easy to use tracker, you'll be able to better see your progress which can be shared with your pharmacist and doctor. Never forget to take your medicines again!

- Pharmacy Chat: Chat with a pharmacist from your local Chemist Warehouse store to seek information regarding your medications and general pharmacy advice to help you get well and keep you feeling great.

- Store Details: Find all the details of you favourite Chemist Warehouse store or locate any Chemist Warehouse store across Australia. Trading hours, phone numbers and locations information is available in the App. We're never too far away! 

The Chemist Warehouse App is a complete platform for any busy individual who wants to take better control of their health and enjoys the convenience of having their medicines and pharmacy goods ready ahead of time.

Our focus at Chemist Warehouse is to assist every Australian to live, look and feel well. Chemist Warehouse is the home of big brands and real savings.

Get the App today and start taking control of your wellness. It's wellness at your fingertips.

Accessing your images has never been easier with Queensland X-Ray. 

Use our App any time of the day or night to:

·       access your images and reports (after your scan)
·       share your results with family, friends or medical professionals
·       Request an appointment
·       update your email and password
·       Manage notifications for your images and your reports

How does it work?

Already registered for the Queensland X-Ray Patient Portal? Log in using your mobile phone number and password.

If you haven’t registered, ask one of our team members at your next appointment for instructions on how. You will be asked for your mobile number and email address, including your authorisation to receive a text to register. You will then receive an SMS message containing a link to create your account. 

Once you have an account you can log in at any time to see your images and your reports. Your reports will be uploaded 14 days after we have authorised and sent the report to your referring doctor.

It’s important for you to go back to your doctor to get your results, so we won’t send them until you’ve had time to make that appointment. Our doctors will always personally call your doctor if the scans show anything unexpected.

You can also perform these functions on our website at patient.qldxray.com.au

Support for our App is available at portalsupport@qldxray.com.au

The Our Medical app places access to exceptional healthcare at your fingertips. Connect to your healthcare information and the network of General Practitioners at our medical centres. 

GP CHECK-IN
Discreetly check-in to see a bulk billing GP in a few taps. Choose between the doctor of your choice, or the first available GP. We’ll also remind you which doctor you saw on your last visit. 

PLACE IN QUEUE UPDATES
After you have checked-in, you can track your place in the GP queue – see the number of patients in front of you and an indication of wait-time. You will be provided with real-time updates on your place in the queue and can switch from a requested doctor, to first available.

GP ROSTERS
Check the roster for your preferred GP up to two weeks in advance, so you can plan your visit.

eSCRIPTS
eScripts issued by your doctor will be stored in your eScript wallet. Show the eScript to the pharmacy to dispense on the spot, or order online.

HEALTH DOCUMENTS
Receive electronic copies of correspondence from your doctor including medical certificates, specialist referrals, and radiology and pathology reports. You will also receive notifications when test results have been returned to your referring GP, so you know when to come back to discuss your results.

MANAGE ALLIED APPOINTMENTS
Appointments with allied health professionals, such as physiotherapists, or Specialists can be booked and managed via the app.

MANAGE YOUR INFO
Keep contact information for you and your dependants, and Medicare, DVA, Pensioner and Health Care Card details up to date. You can also link dependants to your account so you can check-in on their behalf. 

MEMBERSHIP PROGRAM
The Our Medical Membership Program gives you exclusive access to healthcare benefits including vouchers for dental and physio. 

About Our Medical
Our Medical offers exceptional healthcare for all. Our network of medical centres provide access to comprehensive healthcare services including general practice, radiology, pathology, dental, and accident and emergency. No appointment is required to see a bulk billing GP. Open every day until 10pm

The FreeStyle LibreLink app is approved for use with FreeStyle Libre and FreeStyle Libre 2 system sensors. You can check your glucose by scanning your sensor with your phone. Now FreeStyle Libre 2 system sensor users can get automatic glucose readings in the FreeStyle LibreLink app, updated every minute, and also receive alarms when your glucose is low or high. [1][2]

You can use the FreeStyle LibreLink app to:

* View your current glucose reading, trend arrow and glucose history
* Receive low or high glucose alarms with FreeStyle Libre 2 system sensors [2]
* Add notes to track your food, insulin use and exercise
* See reports, such as Time in Range and Daily Patterns
* Share your data with your doctor and family, with your permission [3]

SMARTPHONE COMPATIBILITY
Compatibility may vary between phones and operating systems. Learn more about compatible phones at https://www.freestylelibre.com.au.

USING YOUR APP AND READER WITH THE SAME SENSOR
Alarms can only be issued on your FreeStyle Libre 2 reader or your phone (not both). To receive alarms on your phone, you must start the sensor with the app. To receive alarms on your FreeStyle Libre 2 reader, you must start the sensor with your reader. Once the sensor has been started with the reader, you can also scan that sensor with your phone.

Remember that the app and reader do not share data with each other. For complete information on a device, scan your sensor every eight hours with that device; otherwise, your reports will not include all your data. You can upload and view data from all of your devices on LibreView.com.

APP INFORMATION
FreeStyle LibreLink is intended for measuring glucose levels in people with diabetes when used with a sensor. For more information on how to use FreeStyle LibreLink, refer to the User’s Manual, which can be accessed through the app. If you require a printed User’s Manual, contact Abbott Diabetes Care Customer Support.

Consult a healthcare professional to confirm if this product is right for you or if you have questions about how to use this product to make treatment decisions.

Learn more at http://FreeStyleLibre.com.

[1] If you are using the FreeStyle LibreLink app, you must also have access to a blood glucose monitoring system, as the app does not provide one.  

[2] Alarms that you receive do not include your glucose reading, so you must scan your sensor to check your glucose.

[3] Use of FreeStyle LibreLink and LibreLinkUp requires registration with LibreView.

The sensor housing, FreeStyle, Libre, and related brand marks are marks of Abbott. Other trademarks are the property of their respective owners.

For additional legal notices and terms of use, go to http://FreeStyleLibre.com.

========

To resolve any technical or Customer Service issues that you are having with a FreeStyle Libre product, please contact FreeStyle Libre Customer Service directly.

myPRP is used by patients to securely access images and reports of scans performed at a PRP Diagnostic Imaging practice. You may also request appointments through this app.

When your results are ready to view, you will receive an SMS message containing a link to a registration instructions page with an activation code. You will need to use this code to activate your account and set a password. You will be able to use your account to access to all future studies performed at any practice in the PRP Imaging network.

The 'Request an Appointment' feature allows you to organise a visit to one of our practices. Please enter details of the imaging required and upload a photo of the referral form filled out by your doctor. Our friendly staff will then contact you to organise and confirm the appointment.

If you need assistance with myPRP please email myprp@prpimaging.com.au with a description of the problem.

For more information about PRP Imaging visit www.prpimaging.com.au

Please Note: Your doctor will be able to access your images and report as soon as they are available. You should always return to your doctor to discuss your results.

* Over 3 million skin checks 
SkinVision is a medical service that provides an immediate risk assessment.
Skin checks with our clinically validated technology are affordable and potentially covered by your health insurance provider. You can buy a single risk assessment or purchase unlimited checks to effectively monitor your moles for 3 or 12 months (no subscription).

You can use some features of SkinVision for free including our risk profile and skin type quizzes, storing images of your moles and accessing UV information in your area.
Our checks use an algorithm to assess your mole or skin spot for suspicious signs. Our service is quality assured by our team of dermatology experts. Our users have received more than 3.5 million risk assessments.

The SkinVision app is a regulated medical device with European CE marking. We care about your privacy and are ISO certified for information security and the quality management system. SkinVision is trusted by insurance companies worldwide for skin health. SkinVision has partnerships with leading health insurers, dermatology clinics and research universities in the United Kingdom, Australia, Germany, the Netherlands, and New Zealand.

WHY SKINVISION?
Dermatologists recommend checking your skin spots at least every 3 months.
Monitoring spots can help you to identify suspicious signs at an early stage. By using SkinVision, you can:
- Receive an immediate risk indication for your mole or skin spot.
- Store your photos to help monitor changes over time and easily share them with your doctor.

CONNECT WITH SKINVISION
Instagram - https://www.instagram.com/sknvsn/
If you have any questions or comments about the service, please contact us at info@skinvision.com.

Take charge of your sleep therapy success with myAir™, an exclusive app available to Resmed AirSense™ and AirCurve™ users.

GUIDED SETUP

Whether you set up your equipment at home or in person, myAir helps you get started with confidence and ease. The Personal Therapy Assistant* feature provides interactive voice-guided instructions to help you set up your equipment and fit your mask. myAir's Test Drive* feature helps you get comfortable with therapy using your machine at different levels of air pressure. The app also offers a Library of helpful videos and guides that show you how to set up your specific AirSense or AirCurve machine and Resmed mask, as well as how to get comfortable on therapy.

PERSONALISED SUPPORT

Getting used to therapy can take a little time, but with the right support you can enjoy a great night's sleep. myAir acts like your personal sleep coach. It guides you through therapy and connects you to the support you need, when you need it.

myAir offers tailored coaching, tips and videos to increase your comfort and success. For example, if you have problems with your mask seal, myAir will provide tips about how to fix it. The app also offers a full Library of helpful videos and guides to answer common questions.

Along the way, you'll get email and push notifications that encourage and support you. With regular check-ins*, myAir proactively prompts you to see how your therapy is going and provides coaching if you have problems. With your prior consent, myAir also shares your therapy insights with your healthcare team* so they can be more connected to your care.

SLEEP THERAPY TRACKING

With myAir, you can easily access your daily sleep therapy data to monitor your therapy progress. Simply log in to see your nightly myAir score, which shows how well you slept on therapy at a glance. Detailed metrics help you track your therapy progress over time. You can also download a therapy summary report to keep for your records or share with your healthcare provider.

INTEGRATED WITH HEALTH APPLICATIONS 

myAir integrates with Apple Health and Health Connect to display the health data you track alongside your Resmed therapy data.

Learn more at Resmed.com/myAir.

*Feature available only with an AirSense 11 machine. Not available with AirSense 10 or AirCurve 10. 

Note: myAir is available only for Resmed AirSense and AirCurve machines with built-in wireless connectivity. For the AirMini™ machine, please download the AirMini by Resmed app.

Always seek the advice of a physician or other qualified health provider with any questions you may have regarding a medical condition. If you think you are experiencing a medical emergency, seek immediate medical attention.

developer: The Trustee for Coburg Medical Imaging Trust
description:
At Vision Radiology we are passionate about innovating Radiology to improve patient care and outcomes. Vision Radiology App is an integrated app which gives patients fast and easy access to images and reports on mobile, tablet and desktop.

The app is simple and intuitive, with the ability to quickly search through your images and reports.

​As a patient, you will continue to have peace of mind knowing that all your images and reports are stored with the highest security, enabling secure access, tracking and auditing. 

The images will be available 2 hours after you have completed your examination at Vision Radiology. The report will be released to your app within a 7 day timeframe, this allows you enough time to discuss the results with your doctors.

For all further information, please email info@visionradiology.com.au, alternatively contact one of our clinics directly.

The Qscan Patient Results app offers you the convenience of accessing and managing your medical imaging and reports right from your smartphone or tablet. With this user-friendly app, you can easily view and share your reports and images in one centralised location.

The app is ideal if:
 - You suffer from a long-term medical condition and need your imaging history.
 - You are pregnant and would like to share your precious baby scans with family or friends.
 - You would like to share scans with other health professionals such as a physiotherapist or chiropractor.
 - You travel and need to access your scans anywhere, anytime.

You can download the patient app from the App Store or by visiting patient.qscan.com.au. If you encounter any difficulties accessing your results through the app, please visit qscan.zed.link for assistance.

For more detailed information about Qscan and its services, please visit our website qscan.com.au/patientaccess

Please remember to always consult with your healthcare professional for a proper medical evaluation and interpretation of your results.

IA X-rays allows patients to view, share and store radiology images performed at an Imaging Associates’ clinic. Patients can access their images 24/7.

Our platform gives you secure online access to your images via computer, tablet or phone.

You have access to your images anywhere, anytime allowing you to share with anyone you choose – whether showing your impressive baby ultrasounds to family via social media or sharing with a health professional while travelling. Granting access to medical practitioners is simple and quick. IA X-rays is an ecological solution reducing the need to store and manage films and other devices (USBs, CDs etc) – no need to remember and carry your films to your next appointment.

X-rays and scans are an important part of your medical history. Our platform allows you to upload previous scans or scans from other imaging groups so you have your complete history in one convenient place.

Imaging Associates Group is an independent diagnostic imaging practice which is owned and operated by a team of dedicated Radiologists. We have established private practices in Box Hill and Mitcham as well as our Regional practice in Wagga Wagga to provide specialised imaging services to practitioners and patients in our local communities.  Our group of sub-specialised Radiologists are led by experienced Clinical Directors – Drs Paul Marks, Daniel Lee, York Cheung and Chris Holden – to offer expertise and experience across a comprehensive range of services including Low Dose CT, Ultrasound, X-ray, MRI, Mammography, Fluoroscopy and DXA.

For more information please call 03 8843 7999 or email images@imagingassociates.net.au

Take your learning with you! Ausmed is a simple way to access a wide range of healthcare knowledge and improve the quality of your care. Plus, it gives you everything you need to meet your CPD requirements.

The latest evidence-based content
All our learning activities are developed with healthcare experts and we regularly review them to ensure you're getting recent and accurate information.

Meet your CPD requirement
You can document your learning to keep track of CPD requirements. Use the learning planning tool to save resources for later, so you don't miss out as you explore our learning catalogue.

Fits in your pocket and your schedule
With our app, you can find time for a little learning whenever it suits you – between shifts, on your commute or over a break.

Your kind of healthcare
Ausmed has a wide library of learning resources that cover topics for Nurses, Midwives, Paramedics, Pharmacists and more! That also includes Healthcare Workers in the Disability, Aged Care, and Community and Home Care sectors.

We're here to help
At Ausmed, we're always looking for ways to improve the quality of your learning and help you use your time efficiently. You can use our learning guides to support your positive habit-building and time management.

Stay in control of your progress
You can manage your own learning reports, which means it's really simple to download and verify that you've met your requirements.

Choose the format that suits you
Depending on how much time you have and how you prefer to learn, you can engage with our learning resources as articles, video lectures or courses.

Access to unlimited expert-reviewed learning activities
New and up-to-date learning activities added each week
